uk.ac.macaulay.util
Enum PartialOrderComparison

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<PartialOrderComparison>
      uk.ac.macaulay.util.PartialOrderComparison
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<PartialOrderComparison>
public enum PartialOrderComparison
extends java.lang.Enum<PartialOrderComparison>

PartialOrderComparison A result from a comparison of partially ordered objects. Methods are provided enabling an idiom such as the following:

PartialOrderComparable<Object> obj1;
PartialOrderComparable<Object> obj2;

if(obj1.partialOrderCompareTo(obj2).less()) {
  // Do something if obj1 < obj2
}

Though of course, one could just as well do obj1.partialOrderCompareTo(obj2) == PartialOrderComparison.LESS_THAN in the boolean expression. However, this is more verbose.

Author:
Gary Polhill

generalise

public PartialOrderComparison generalise(PartialOrderComparison that)
Generalise a partial order comparison result. The generalisation of two results is the same as the strict generalisation, except that the generalisation of EQUAL_TO and MORE_THAN is MORE_THAN, and the generalisation of EQUAL_TO and LESS_THAN is LESS_THAN.

Parameters:
that - The result to generalise this one with.
Returns:
The generalisation.

strictGeneralise

public PartialOrderComparison strictGeneralise(PartialOrderComparison that)
Generalise a partial order comparison result strictly. The strict generalisation of two results is INCOMPARABLE unless they are both the same.

Parameters:
that - The partial order comparison result to generalise this one with.
Returns:
The strict generalisation.
